reviews.text: The ambiance and food are both great at this  restaurant.  I had the vegetarian ratatouille, and it was simply delicious.  The only complaint or drawback of this place is that there are no on-site washrooms....if you need to use the washroom they tell you to go down the street to a public toilet...?  If you expect your dining guests to have dinner and drinks for a couple of hours at your restaurant,  you should expect that they might need to need to use the washroom? I wonder if the employees also use the public washrooms down the street?

Great service, good food and we love the atmosphere there. I often come with friends or alone with my baby and I’m always well looked after. 
Portions are generous and coffees are good. 
Love it on a Sunday but it does get crowded! Weekdays are perfect.
It is an average eatery for a quick lunch and coffee. Menu is limited with few options. Food quality is average too. Outside seating is nice with street view in good location.

I saw a cockroach next to the trays holding the pastries on the counter. There seemed to be no concerted effort by the employees there to thoroughly clean up after me and another separate customer who arrived in front of me pointed it out.

I saw the cashier throw away one offending pastry (presumably pointed out by other customer) but no other efforts to find and eliminate the cockroach.

This is very concerning. I understand that Hong Kong has vermin but as a restaurant, all efforts must be taken to maintain a hygienic environment for serving food.

Love the fresh french food served here! The spreads available on every table to go with their oh so fresh french baguatte, need a seperate page altogether! The food is just a part of the whole experience- the outdoor dining, the music in thr background and a very friendly staff! Highly recommend when you are around this area and are looking for brunch options!
